Morocco,Q3s8L_fjHjU,UgxNWWN_gsMEVgOynGR4AaABAg.AUPqyKDTyP2AUQ0bba5YJ3,UgxNWWN_gsMEVgOynGR4AaABAg,@mohameda2474,"​​@TraceTheGlobe  
-Boujloud festival every year in popular old neighborhoods of Agadir (dcheira for example).
-Famous Taghazout village surf.
-Amlou in the Famous Souk el hedd old traditional market.
-Souk inezgane the first biggest old economic city centre of Morocco.
-Agadir oufela forteresse built to chase Portuguese empire in founty coast between ~1450.
-imouzar idaoutanan waterfall.
-Berber women traditional clothes in Tiznit which represent feminity and freedom with unicorn jewelry = like unicorn of liberty status of NY.
-Gold and silver Berber jewelry souk founded by Jews in Tiznit since centuries and it's forteresse old wall.
-Taroudant big forteresse wall (surround all the city) to protect saadiyine king from Ottoman empire ~ 1500 because they killed his father.
""Morocco is divided in two,"" Marshal Lyautey once said. ""Useful Morocco,"" that of the coast and the plains the richest one, and ""useless"" Morocco, that of the mountains and the Berber tribes. 
From a tourism perspective, Morocco needs to develop mountain tourism. Access to the Anti-Atlas (for example) is currently very limited in terms of services offered in the mountains, but it is entirely possible to develop tourist circuits in the mountains and facilitate access to tourist services so that these mountainous regions, unknown to tourists, become more visible. I am sure that this will be a remedy for people seeking spiritual fulfillment, serenity, and peace of mind in their lives especially in summer times where the sky is shinning at night under stars everywhere even if it's so hot at August",2026-03-16T12:34:32Z,2026-03-16T12:36:21Z,0,True,,2026-05-11T02:01:20.356115
