Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,Ugyt4qFUfrs1Gz4eG2p4AaABAg,,@Jer-7007,"Well, I'm glad to see that you liked it.  But I doubt if anyone from your generation will understand the political context of the story (which would have been well understood by audiences of the time).  At this time, Casablanca (which is in Morocco) was a French colony.  But Germany had conquered France in WWII.  This meant that France, itself, was under German rule.  But French colonies (like Morocco) were kind of on their own.  That's why the French colonial police chief in this movie (Renault) , wants to enforce French law, but must kind of defer to his German masters - which he opposes sentimentally.  This is a delicate political situation,  well known to people of the time but that most people of this time wouldn't understand.",2026-05-04T09:47:30Z,2026-05-04T09:47:30Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-11T02:01:32.469152
