Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,UgzmKRtK0Im-HRQ0oKp4AaABAg,,@jcortese3300,"One thing a lot of people miss is that Yvonne's arc was exactly a precis of Rick's.  Rick jilts her and then says, ""I never plan that far ahead,"" which is the same as Ilsa, who said, ""That's too far ahead to plan,"" the day before she fails to show up at the train station.

And after being jilted by Rick, Yvonne makes a similar decision to him -- she stops caring, puts herself first, and starts playing both sides, even flirting with German officers despite being French.

But Victor Laszlo's gesture, having the band play ""La Marseillaise,"" reminds her of her roots and she rejects the German.

Her own short character arc is a perfect micro-version of Rick's.",2026-05-03T23:08:44Z,2026-05-03T23:08:44Z,1,False,0.0,2026-05-11T02:01:32.469186
