Rabat,BcpnamTxNzE,UgxY_W-g1ojnLSdEuah4AaABAg,,@gon20hig,"Chellah (Shalla) and Hassan Mosque are two major historical sites in Rabat closely linked to Amazigh history. Chellah was originally inhabited by local Amazigh populations .the site later became the Roman city of Sala Colonia in the 1st century AD. During the Amazigh Almohad period in the 12th century, Chellah regained importance as a sacred area, before being developed into a fortified necropolis under the Amazigh Marinid dynasty in the 13th–14th centuries. Hassan Mosque and its minaret (Hassan Tower) were commissioned by Yaqub al-Mansur, an Amazigh Almohad caliph, around 1191–1197 CE, as part of an ambitious project to make Rabat an imperial capital, but construction stopped after his death in 1199 CE, leaving the tower unfinished and symbolic of Almohad architectural power.",2026-01-26T17:09:06Z,2026-01-26T17:09:06Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-11T02:01:45.729561
