Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgwiR88FdHN5J_juEhx4AaABAg.AAMz98HqXAEAAOLADEvT0j,UgwiR88FdHN5J_juEhx4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Darn it, Enrique. How frustrating, and I've had similar happen to me as well. Thanks for the recommendation in Granada. We will add it to our wish list when we visit Granada! Thank you so much for watching! —Judy",2024-11-03T18:27:48Z,2024-11-03T18:27:48Z,2,True,,2026-05-11T02:02:08.070019
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgwiR88FdHN5J_juEhx4AaABAg.AAMz98HqXAEAI9l0kdrr0j,UgwiR88FdHN5J_juEhx4AaABAg,@tims7639,@FindingGinaMariethe Alhambra and the Generalife are absolutely astonishing.  Incredible glimpse into the Moorish past of Al-Andalus!,2025-05-15T22:44:58Z,2025-05-15T22:44:58Z,0,True,,2026-05-11T02:02:08.070036
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgyVFtStcJk5QZiTCUB4AaABAg.AAM_dMQToZVAAOM4dQZS1q,UgyVFtStcJk5QZiTCUB4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"It was such an incredible experience. We highly recommend you see Fes if you can as well (and do a Sahara Desert experience if you can!). Fes and Marrakech are vastly different in many ways, but at their core, there are wonderfully kind people in both. Let us know if you have any questions we should incorporate into any of our Morocco series before the final two episodes are released! —Judy
