Tangier,SCT1LbOFEaE,Ugx3q9OA1qsBw79wWsp4AaABAg,,@fouedfoued5692,"_Tangier , indeed can boast of being one of the very few cities on earth where almost all the great civilizations have felt attracted and drawn to for they've all left their mark or legacy , from the Levant Phoenicians (more than a millennium b.c) , followed by the Greeks , then the Roman till the Syrio-Arab Umayyads...Tangier is one the few emplacements where Gods and winds collide , where Heracles defeated the God Antaeus (Greek mytho|ogy) , after that the Greek Colossus seized the Golden Apple in Lixus (Today's Larache).._
_Tangier the Silent witness of one of the biggest naval collisions between the British Nelson’s fleet (Which was frequently stationed in front of Cap Spartel) Vs the Napoleon's Franco-Spanish great Armada in the Trafalgar campaign in the Strait of G¡braltar l8o5.._
