AFCON,CdWcGc47Rv8,Ugzfmv0IcuiefmaZLT94AaABAg,,@oulaich,"The truth about the AFCON 2025 final is simple: Football is governed by laws, not by who puts more pressure on the referee. When the Senegalese team decided to walk off the pitch for nearly 15 minutes in the 83rd minute, they didn’t just protest a call—they officially forfeited the match under CAF Regulations.
​According to Articles 82 and 84 of the tournament rules, any team that refuses to play or leaves the ground before the end of the match is considered the loser by a 3-0 scoreline. It is also important to recognize the impossible position the referee was put in. Faced with a complete walk-off and massive pressure from his superiors to avoid a total riot in the stands or further chaos on the field, he was forced to restart a game that legally should have ended right then and there.
​By forcing a restart on their own terms after such a long delay, Senegal disrupted the spirit of the final and ruined the celebration for millions. You cannot pause a continental final for 15 minutes and then expect the result to stand. Morocco stayed on the pitch, respected the referee, and followed the professional code of conduct. No matter what happened in extra time, the match was legally over the moment they walked toward the tunnel. Rules are rules, and in Rabat, the rule of law prevailed over the chaos.",2026-03-22T22:20:39Z,2026-03-22T22:20:39Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-11T02:03:09.550421
