Tourisme,z76IT0xSeBc,UgxrTF7f7925Q8SW2RV4AaABAg,,@kazuoyoshioka4690,"phillipine can get out of poverty, if they do this.
1) educate their people and specially the kids in school.
A. Being independent(standing on their own feet, not relying on others) is vital for modern society, both USA and Japan is very similar in that it's citizens values indepenncy, when US was developping, people encourage independency, when japan was poor and developping, it's citizens take pride in being independent, one samurai who is considered father of modern japanese capitalism, when he was young, he was so poor, he had to eat rat to survive, he had no food, but he never asked his rich dad for money, he is samurai, so he have to live by himself, not relying on other even their parents.
Getting out of poverty by your own strength alone creates strong mindset and competent individual, it gives man self respect and confidence.
Phillipine got influence badly by US's money worshipping culture, people in phillipines become so obsessed with money that, they would even lie to get money, too many people did it, it become the norm.
But they don't understand that both US and Japan, the most important virtue of business is being honest.
Warren buffett said, no one wants to do business with liers, so being honest and good human being is more profitable in long run.
And essesntial for stable business and stability of the society.
Japan is same thing, 18th century japanese philosopher  named Baigan Ishida wrote a book about business ethics and it was one of the best seller of the time in japan, he gave story of rich and successful merchant had a 2 son, he needed to decide which one will inherit his shop and money.
His eldest bright and talented kid, one day he scammed his customer, his servants finds out and fixed it, then master of the house finds out, the servant begged the master to forgive his son, since customer never found out the defect in the product and service and they fixed it before anyone can find out.
And the eldest son is very smart and talented kid, he should forgive him.
The father merchant, the master of the house said, dishonest man is not suited to be merchant, send him to be peasant.
And master of the house appointed his 2nd son, who is not as smart as his eldest son but had honest heart to be his successor.

This was taught as basis of japanese businessman.
Even to this day, japanese businessman values trust and honesty more than anything.
American business man are same thing, honesty, integrity is the most important mindset and virtue to be businessman.

Phillipino only learned money worshipping from americans, but never learned the importance of how honesty and trustworthyness is vital for the business and economy from Americans.

Also both japanese and americans are frugal, regular pinoys likes to spend money, but not think about saving money.

Phillipines needs to glorify, individualism, independency, frugality, honesty and integrity(specially in business).
They could become rich.

They think scamming people gets people rich.
It's wrong.
Those people who stole money, they are making bad example for the country and people.
It encourages bad behaviour and keeps everyone poor.
It makes foreighners look down on phillipinos.
It makes the entire phillipino community look bad and untrustworthy.
If pinoys love their country and family, they need to punish those who do scam business and lies.
Then encourage the virtue of independency, not rely on others, frugality, save money, and do honest work.
It's hard and it make take time, but do this phillipine will eventually become wealthier.

Honesty and good heart.
Do not worry about money,
Seek the kingdom of god first, then everything will be added unto you.
The lord said this and it is true.
The wicked and evil only prospers for little while, but they will go down.
Only the honest good work last long.",2026-05-05T01:31:34Z,2026-05-05T01:31:34Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-11T02:03:57.444173
