Tourisme,tQG5jBBGn2Q,UgyPIYKpZU8WYLJRAi14AaABAg,,@vaughan6998,"Interesting observations Callum. Thank you.
SA and Rhodesians have been migrating to Western Australia for about 60 years. They are not a natural fit for Australians. Something to do with their overt racism. Australia is a very racist society itself, but we are a bit fair as well. We hate the Israelis just as much as the Gazans. I think we are suspicious of SA's, in the same way we might be suspicious of a Russian or a Serbian on first meeting.
The US navy used to call into Fremantle, and I saw a black sailor trying to unsuccessfully chat up a 30 year old blonde woman, in the street outside a shop. From a doorway on the other side of the road, a 6'4"" SA guy calls out in his booming SA accent ""Hey, you black bastard, leave our women alone. Get back to your ship. Get your black arse out of here, NOW"". He left.
No Australian would ever say that. Perhaps....""Come on mate, piss off, you can see she is not interested"" would be OK to say. Many SA's I have met, wish they were still kicking the Kaffers around back home. The rest of them are delightful.
I also heard a woman teacher from SA say how 'wonderfully safe' she felt walking in the Australian bush. Unless you are swimming with the sharks and crocodiles, there are no dangerous animals in Australia. She was not talking about Leopards jumping down from trees etc. She said that as a woman walking by herself in the SA bush, she would anticipate being raped and murdered, before being eaten by a wild animal. Not really on the same level as 'a Dingo eating your baby' is it?",2026-05-09T14:23:00Z,2026-05-09T14:23:00Z,2,False,0.0,2026-05-11T02:03:58.827380
